# Gen-AI Feature Guide

## How It Works (Team Overview)

A user types a prompt — from the sidebar chat or the on-canvas star — and the system creates (or updates) objects on the canvas with live controls in the properties panel.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A([User types a prompt]) --> B{What's selected?}

    B -->|Nothing selected| C{What kind of request?}
    B -->|Object with controls| D[Collect object info\n+ existing controls]
    B -->|Plain objects| E[Collect selection info]

    D --> C
    E --> C

    C -->|Image grid\ne.g. 'photo grid'| F[Run local template\nNo AI needed — instant]
    C -->|Everything else| G[Send to AI]

    G --> H["AI picks from its toolbox\n(generators, controls, actions)\nbased on the prompt"]

    H --> I["AI writes a response:\n• A generator program\n• A set of controls\n• Canvas actions"]

    F --> J
    I --> J[Create / update objects\non the canvas]

    J --> K[Controls appear in\nthe properties panel]

    K --> L{User adjusts\na control}
    L -->|Generator exists| M[Re-run the program\nlocally — instant]
    L -->|No generator| N[Apply the single\nproperty change]

    M --> J
    N --> J

    K --> O{User types\na follow-up prompt}
    O -->|e.g. 'add a size slider'| G

    style A fill:#333,color:#fff,stroke:#555
    style F fill:#2a7a2a,color:#fff,stroke:#3a9a3a
    style J fill:#2a7a2a,color:#fff,stroke:#3a9a3a
    style K fill:#2a7a2a,color:#fff,stroke:#3a9a3a
    style H fill:#444,color:#fff,stroke:#666
```

**The key ideas:**
- **One prompt, two outputs.** The AI returns both canvas objects *and* controls to manipulate them.
- **Controls live on the object.** Close the file, reopen it, share it — the controls come with the layer.
- **After the first AI call, everything runs locally.** Dragging a slider re-runs the generator program in the browser. No network call, no waiting.
- **Some things skip AI entirely.** Image grids use a built-in template — they run instantly with zero API cost.
- **Follow-up prompts refine the tool.** Say "add a padding slider" and the AI rewrites the generator while preserving everything already built.
- **Auto-generate (the "+" button)** skips the prompt entirely. Select an object, click "+", and the AI reverse-engineers controls from its existing properties.

